<h4><a name="_RefSort">Sorting and Filtering</a></h4>
<p>The list of games may be sorted by any column.  Click on the column header
name to sort the games in ascending order by that column.  Click on the same column again
to sort the games in descending order by that column.</p>

<p>You may also filter the game list by column(s).  Filters may be applied to any column
from a combo box below its title.  You may select a pre-defined filter from the drop-down list of the
combo box or define your own filter by typing one in the combo box.  Filters restrict the game list
to only games that match the filter.  For instance, if you enter <i>Bob</i> in the game name column
filter, only games that begin with <i>Bob</i> will appear.  Certain columns support more advanced
filters that allow comparisons (<, <=, >, >=).  Check the sample filters for each column to see examples
of what is supported.  To remove filtering for a column, select <i>No Filter</i> from the drop-down list.</p>

<p>You may also add your own custom filters and remove filters (including sample filters) for each
column.  To add, enter the filter in the combo box and select <i>Add</i> in the drop-down list.  To
remove a filter, select select the filter from the drop-down list or enter the filter in the combo box,
then select <i>Remove</i> in the drop-down list.  You may reset all filters to their default list
in the
<a href="OptionsTab.html">Options Tab</a>.</p>

